entities.name: mooshroom
entities.popup:
Before you start...

In Minecraft, the Mooshroom uses block models for the mushrooms on its back. If you wish to edit the model of these mushrooms, please use the "Mooshroom [Mushrooms]" custom model.

entities.name: mooshroom_mushrooms
entities.description: A custom version of the Mooshroom with the mushrooms modelled on top
entities.popup:
Before you start...

This model requires some extra textures in your resource pack to function correctly:

assets/minecraft/textures/entity/cow/red_mushroom.png
assets/minecraft/textures/entity/cow/brown_mushroom.png

These textures need to be created manually, and should be 1x1 transparent images.

They are custom ones added by optifine that overwrite the vanilla mooshroom mushrooms.

Please note, if you were going to use this model to edit the textures independently of the block, you can just use these two textures instead of this model.
